
=Bio=

"Co-founded a worker cooperative on the back of the desktop publishing revolution in 1988, which started my nearly thirty year career working in, for and with cooperatives both in the UK and internationally, with an increasingly digital focus and interest. Self-taught website builder (mainly Drupal) and CiviCRM wrangler. When I'm not helping clients with their web and CRM needs I'm developing projects and strategies under the Cooperative Networks banner: our current project is to create '''an Innovation Cooperative - a global open cooperative platform which itself acts as a development agency for the creation and support of cooperative platforms (more details on this are being developed and published at http://networks.coop)'''. Married with two children, currently living and working in the UK, we have a small finca in Catalunya that we aiming to develop using permaculture techniques, producing high quality olive oil."

